## 4) Fast-answer scenario drills

These are good for MCQ/short-question speed practice.

1. A webpage shows repeated encrypted blocks from a logo image. Which mode was likely used?
2. A file server must recover to data no older than 15 minutes. Which metric matters most?
3. A password manager and Signal are examples of what broad privacy/security idea?
4. A control that says “deny by default and fail securely” belongs to which development area?
5. A security team wants to know “how much damage is tolerable before service must resume.” Which analysis is this?
6. A model answers with unsafe SQL because its output is directly inserted into a database query. What risk is this?
7. A forensic examiner documents every transfer of a USB drive and hash values. What is that called?
8. A company wants to know whether to restore from backup or fail over to a hot site. Which planning area is this?
9. A system encrypts the same plaintext differently every time because it uses a different counter/nonce. Which mode is likely?
10. A team wants to detect malware on endpoints, but also needs evidence for court. Which activity is beyond simple defense?
